# system_contracts.me
# Purpose: Core product lifecycle rules for all booking, payment, credit, waitlist,
#          cancellation, and entitlement flows. These rules define what the product
#          does — not how it is implemented on any given platform.
# Scope: iOS, Android, backend (Supabase Edge Functions, RPCs)

---

## 1. BOOKING LIFECYCLE

### States
A booking may only be in one of these states:
- `confirmed`       — seat is held; payment settled (or free game)
- `waitlisted`      — game is full; player is queued
- `pending_payment` — promoted from waitlist; hold window active; payment not yet complete
- `cancelled`       — booking voided by player or admin

### State Transitions (Allowed)
```
(new)         → confirmed         [player books a free game or completes Stripe payment]
(new)         → waitlisted        [player joins a full game]
waitlisted    → pending_payment   [server promotes player; hold window opened]
pending_payment → confirmed       [player completes Stripe payment within hold window]
pending_payment → waitlisted      [hold expires without payment; player re-queued at position 1]
confirmed     → cancelled         [player or admin cancels]
waitlisted    → cancelled         [player removes themselves from waitlist]
```

### Rules
- DO NOT insert a booking row until payment is complete (Stripe `.completed`) or the game is free.
- DO NOT transition `pending_payment → confirmed` from the client. The client calls `confirmPendingBooking` which PATCHes the DB; the DB is authoritative.
- DO NOT allow a player to hold more than one confirmed or pending_payment seat per game.
- DO NOT allow booking a game with `publish_at > now()` from the public flow. Admins may still see and manage unpublished games.
- Booking `status` enum values in the DB must exactly match the list above. No aliases or variants.


