## 6. SUBSCRIPTION ENTITLEMENTS

### Tiers
- `free` — default. No paid games. No Stripe Connect requirement. Limited game/member capacity.
- `starter` — basic paid features. Stripe Connect required for paid games.
- `pro` — full feature set including analytics, custom branding.
- `enterprise` — custom limits (reserved).

### Entitlement Checks
- `clubs.subscription_tier` is the authoritative field for entitlement checks (denormalised from `club_subscriptions`).
- Feature gates are enforced on the client AND backend Edge Functions.
- Stripe subscription state is synced to `clubs.subscription_tier` via the `stripe-webhook` Edge Function.
- Downgrade: existing data preserved; new paid game creation blocked until tier restored.

### Subscription Payment
- Club owner is billed via Stripe Subscription (not destination charges — separate flow).
- One Stripe Customer per owner (`profiles.stripe_customer_id`), reused across multiple clubs.
- `payment_behavior=default_incomplete`: subscription only activates after first payment succeeds.

---

## VIOLATION IMPACT
- Inserting a booking before Stripe `.completed` → unconfirmed seats; real players locked out; potential double-booking.
- Using a global credit balance → credits from Club A spendable at Club B; incorrect deductions.
- Skipping the 6-hour window check → credits issued for same-day cancellations; financial loss.
- Client-only promotion of waitlist → race conditions; multiple players believe they have the same spot.
- Missing `payment_method` in booking SELECT queries → all attendees shown as "Unpaid" to admins.
